{"ts":"2026-07-11T03:05:51.194Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-fjxm"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-509: pm claim --next lacks candidate filters and race-loss walk — thread next filters + advance to next candidate"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"GH-509 (filed against npm v2026.7.10, which predates PR#502). The base atomic primitive ALREADY shipped: pm claim --next atomically recommends+claims under one lock (pm-114v, PR#502, 2026-07-10). The issue's remaining delta on main: (1) claim --next accepts NONE of pm next's candidate filters (--type/--tag/--priority/--assignee-filter/--parent/--sprint/--release) so a worker cannot scope to its lane — verified via pm claim --help on main 2026-07-11; (2) on race loss the loser fails (exit 4) instead of transparently advancing to the next ready candidate — issue proposes walk-with-bound via --max-attempts <n> / --if-available semantics (claim --next already has --if-available for the single-item case); (3) canonical single-call worker loop: while item=$(pm claim --next --author $AGENT --type task --json); do ...; done. Spelling decision (next --claim vs extending claim --next) belongs to ADR pm-pbyu grammar rules — prefer extending the existing claim --next verb, do not mint a second spelling. Interacts with pm-eqk0: any candidate-walk must ALSO skip Decision-type items or the walk funnels every lane into an unresolvable ADR."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","cli","concurrency","multi-agent"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-11T03:05:51.194Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-11T03:05:51.194Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm claim --next accepts the full pm next candidate-filter set (type/tag/priority/assignee-filter/parent/sprint/release) and scopes ranking identically to pm next; on losing the claim race, claim --next advances to the next ready candidate under the same lock semantics, bounded by --max-attempts (default documented); exhausting candidates returns a distinct non-error empty result usable in shell while-loops; contracts/completions/docs/MCP schema updated per new-flag wiring checklist; no second command spelling introduced"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-dj98"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"38bf6514e2197238660ebe62bed04b17be5887926c337ce2a7c7d365cab09448","message":""}
